			<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1aee8e02303e254e4c217acef7da7e70?s=96&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1aee8e02303e254e4c217acef7da7e70?s=192&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-96 photo' height='96' width='96' loading='lazy'itemprop="image" />					</header><!-- .comment-avatar -->

		<div class="comment-content-wrap">

			<div class="comment-content" itemprop="commentText">
				<p>Thanks for a VERY useful site, Carlton, which I have used several times since HD TV sets came out some years back. Just replaced a 5 year old 50&#8243; plasma set (that developed a horizontal line) with another 51&#8243; plasma set, 720p, ($399), same brand (it was easy to put all the connections in the same places and not have to use a different remote). Our eyes are 9 to10 feet from the screen, and according to your excellent charts and calculator, we would not be able to see any difference between this set and a 1080p set costing several hundred dollars more! Thanks for helping me keep money in my pocket, and keep up the good work!</p>
