		<div class="comment-content-wrap">

			<div class="comment-content" itemprop="commentText">
				<p>What&#8217;s germane to the topic is the resolution of the eye, not the focus. Our eye simply does not have the &#8220;resolution receptors&#8221; to detect the amount of lines that are present in the higher resolution displays at a specific distance.</p>
<div class='jetpack-comment-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-comment-wrapper-3753100-132930-5f84c5858faa0' data-src='https://widgets.wp.com/likes/#blog_id=3753100&amp;comment_id=132930&amp;origin=carltonbale.com&amp;obj_id=3753100-132930-5f84c5858faa0' data-name='like-comment-frame-3753100-132930-5f84c5858faa0'>
