									<div class="comment-meta-block">
						<a itemprop="replyToUrl"rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='https://carltonbale.com/1080p-does-matter/?replytocom=135129#respond' data-commentid="135129" data-postid="218" data-belowelement="comment-135129" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Amol" aria-label='Reply to Amol'>Reply</a>					</div>
											</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

		</div><!-- .comment-content-wrap -->

	</article>

<ol class="children">
<li id="comment-135130" class="comment byuser comment-author-cgbale bypostauthor odd alt depth-2 role-administrator has-avatar" itemprop="comment" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/UserComments">

	<article>
		<header class="comment-avatar">
			<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/114afb9a315344d644806c07989919e1?s=96&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/114afb9a315344d644806c07989919e1?s=192&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-96 photo' height='96' width='96' loading='lazy'itemprop="image" />							<div class="comment-by-author">Author</div>
					</header><!-- .comment-avatar -->

		<div class="comment-content-wrap">

			<div class="comment-content" itemprop="commentText">
				<p>Correct. There is no reason for a 43 inch 4k TV at that viewing distance. </p>
<p>I recommend looking for a TV with HDR. HDR will give a noticeable improvement in picture quality, regardless of resolution or viewing distance. HDR provides benefit.</p>
<div class='jetpack-comment-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-comment-wrapper-3753100-135130-5f84c585aa32a' data-src='https://widgets.wp.com/likes/#blog_id=3753100&amp;comment_id=135130&amp;origin=carltonbale.com&amp;obj_id=3753100-135130-5f84c585aa32a' data-name='like-comment-frame-3753100-135130-5f84c585aa32a'>
